The paper deals with texture analysis and classification, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The proposed approach involves feature extraction using gray tone difference matrixes and local binary patterns, which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing. The use of K-means clustering for database collection is also a common technique in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, the paper also involves aspects of information retrieval (cs.IR), multimedia (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which are all relevant to the proposed approach.
